$ Python: using iter() and open()

The following simple example tries to demonstrate how the built-in functions
→ development/languages/Python/built-in-functions/iter[`iter()`] and
→ development/languages/Python/built-in-functions/open[`open()`] might be used to iterate over each line of a file:

